# Base URL the client uses for all API calls. This is baked in at BUILD time
# (Vite only exposes VITE_* vars to the browser bundle, and only the values
# present when `npm run build` runs).
#
# - Local dev: leave unset. Vite's dev server proxies /api and /uploads to
#   http://localhost:5000 (see vite.config.js), so the default of "/api" works.
# - Production, single-domain deploy (nginx/reverse proxy serves both the
#   built client AND forwards /api to the backend on the same origin): leave
#   as "/api".
# - Production, split-domain deploy (client on Vercel/Netlify, API on
#   Render/Railway/a VPS): set this to the full API origin, e.g.
#   https://api.medpro.co.ke/api
VITE_API_BASE_URL=/api
